  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Transform Africa Organisational Development 2011</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Transform Africa promotes the effectiveness of local organisations in Africa and works in partnership with them to empower poor communities to find lasting solutions to poverty through economic and social transformation processes. One of its core values is to lead by example and spearhead creative approaches to develop the capacity of its partners and ensure that all development initiatives are genuinely driven by the local communities and organisations that serve them. While it has been engaged in the capacity building of its partners for a long time, a recent independent assessment identifies some weaknesses in its strategic planning, governance, advocacy and lobbying, fundraising, and monitoring and evaluation. In these areas it seeks support through a tailored organisation development programme. Gaining excellence in these areas will not only raise its profile and credibility with funding bodies, but will enable it to contribute to knowledge and learning about the role of Diaspora groups within the UK to drive change in developing countries.</narrative>
  </description>
